Definition: offensive to the mind
Example: an abhorrent deed; the obscene massacre at Wounded Knee; morally repugnant customs; repulsive behavior; the most repulsive character in recent novels
Synonyms: noun, feeling, abhorrence, verb, emotion, abhor, detestable, obscene, communication, obscenity, act, repugnant, repugnance, repulsive, attribute, repulsiveness, perception, repel, offensive, to, the, mind, an, deed, massacre, at, Wounded, Knee, morally, customs, behavior, most, character, in, recent, novels
Category: adj.all
